1. The Mechanics of Learning Styles

To select the appropriate memorization technique, it is essential to understand individual learning styles. While most people benefit from a combination, learners generally fall into three categories:

Style	Characteristics	Recommended Strategies
Auditory	Absorbs information best through sound and listening.	Podcasts, recording summaries, reading aloud, and group discussions.
Visual	Retains information through images and spatial organization.	Mind maps, diagrams, videos, and color-coded notes.
Kinesthetic	Learns best through practice, movement, and touch.	Mnemonics involving movement, simulations, and hands-on exercises.


